items.title: Fed Up With the Taliban, Pakistan Expels Masses of Afghans
items.description: Labeling Afghans a national security threat, Pakistan has forced out about a million this year, depriving them of a haven from Afghanistan’s turmoil.

items.title: Deadly Hong Kong Fire Is a Test of Beijing’s Rule in the City
items.description: After Beijing reshaped the political order in Hong Kong in its image, the fire has become a test of how well that new system can govern in a crisis.
